Hi Syera,

Broadcom just provide= an update on this. The reason why the Reporter was crashing is because the= Reporter failed to load the database, and at the same time the database is= corrupted. The Reporter did try to 'fix' the database but it failed. Unfor= tunately the database is not recoverable.

The logs also shows that p= rior to this issue, the Reporter had an issue with the disk space, and stil= l having the same disk space even after the upgrade. This could also caused= the issue prior to the upgrade when you had issue accessing the Reporter G= UI.

From the logs:
Nov 27 15:19:02 reporter monitor_disk_space[13724]: /data now= 90% full

Please run the commands below and provide the = output.

# stop-reporter
# dbbackup list restore
# dbbackup res= tore <number from the list>

Try to restore from the oldest bac= kup.

#start-reporter

If this fails, then the next steps are t= o remove or delete the database and setup a new one, then process the acces= s logs.


Thanks.

Best Regards,
Zulkarnain Janal

Westcon Technical Support (Broadcom Software)
